🧱 CONFIG MODEL

⸻

MetricDefinition
	•	metricName
	•	type (INPUT / THRESHOLD / DERIVED)
	•	aggregationType (MAX / MIN / SUM / AVG)
	•	inputMetrics (dependencies)

⸻

Threshold
	•	metricName
	•	minValue
	•	maxValue
	•	status (int: 1=GREEN, 2=YELLOW, 3=RED)

⸻

⚙️ ENGINE DESIGN (CRITICAL)

⸻

🔹 STEP 1: Compile Config → Execution Plan

Create an ExecutionPlan:

class ExecutionStep {
    String metricName;
    MetricType type;
    AggregationType aggregationType;
    int[] inputIndexes;
}

	•	Build DAG from metric definitions
	•	Validate no cycles
	•	Perform topological sort
	•	Convert metric names → index mapping
	•	Store as ordered steps

⸻

🔹 STEP 2: Data Representation (VERY IMPORTANT)

Use primitive arrays:

int[][] metricValues; 
// metricValues[metricIndex][entityIndex]

	•	Avoid Map<String, Object>
	•	Avoid object creation inside loops

⸻

🔹 STEP 3: Vectorized Execution

DO NOT process per entity.

Instead:

for (ExecutionStep step : steps) {
    for (int i = 0; i < entityCount; i++) {
        // compute metric for all entities
    }
}


⸻

🔹 STEP 4: Threshold Optimization

Precompile threshold into fast logic:

if (value < 3) return 1;
else if (value < 5) return 2;
else return 3;

Avoid looping over threshold arrays.

⸻

🔹 STEP 5: Derived Metrics

Use numeric status:
	•	GREEN → 1
	•	YELLOW → 2
	•	RED → 3

Aggregation:
	•	MAX → worst
	•	MIN → best

⸻

🔹 STEP 6: Scenario Execution
	•	Run BASE (no overrides)
	•	Apply overrides (values + thresholds)
	•	Run SCENARIO
	•	Compare results

